@page "/"

<PageTitle>nuget-ai demos</PageTitle>

<section class="overview-grid">
	<article class="demo-card featured-card">
		<p class="eyebrow">Search</p>
		<h2>Romania search</h2>
		<p>Compare breadth-first search, uniform-cost search, and A* on the standard AIMA Romania map with visible frontier, explored states, priorities, and path progression. Built around <code>Italbytz.AI.Search</code>.</p>
		<a class="primary-link" href="romania-search">Launch demo</a>
	</article>

	<article class="demo-card featured-card">
		<p class="eyebrow">Search</p>
		<h2>Weighted Graph</h2>
		<p>Step through Dijkstra on small weighted graphs and inspect relaxations, distances, and the evolving shortest-path tree. Built around <code>Italbytz.AI.Search</code>.</p>
		<a class="primary-link" href="weighted-graph">Launch demo</a>
	</article>

	<article class="demo-card accent-card">
		<p class="eyebrow">Adversarial search</p>
		<h2>Tic-Tac-Toe</h2>
		<p>Compare minimax and alpha-beta pruning on compact Tic-Tac-Toe positions and inspect how move ordering reduces the number of expanded states. Built around <code>Italbytz.AI.Search.Adversarial</code>.</p>
		<a class="primary-link" href="tic-tac-toe">Launch demo</a>
	</article>

	<article class="demo-card muted-card">
		<p class="eyebrow">Adversarial search</p>
		<h2>Two-Ply</h2>
		<p>Inspect a compact depth-2 game tree and compare minimax with alpha-beta pruning under different move-order scenarios. Built around <code>Italbytz.AI.Search.Adversarial</code>.</p>
		<a class="primary-link" href="two-ply">Launch demo</a>
	</article>

	<article class="demo-card accent-card">
		<p class="eyebrow">Optimization</p>
		<h2>Linear Programming</h2>
		<p>Contrast the LP relaxation with the ILP optimum on a two-variable problem and inspect the feasible polygon, integer lattice points, and shifted optimum. Built around <code>Italbytz.AI.Search.Continuous</code>.</p>
		<a class="primary-link" href="linear-programming">Launch demo</a>
	</article>

	<article class="demo-card muted-card">
		<p class="eyebrow">Optimization</p>
		<h2>N-Queens: Local Search</h2>
		<p>Compare hill climbing, simulated annealing, and a genetic algorithm on the same 8-queens board with visible conflicts and step-by-step metrics. Constraint evaluation is tied to <code>Italbytz.AI.CSP</code>.</p>
		<a class="primary-link" href="n-queens-search">Launch demo</a>
	</article>

	<article class="demo-card featured-card">
		<p class="eyebrow">Decision making</p>
		<h2>GridWorld MDP</h2>
		<p>Compare value iteration and policy iteration on the classic stochastic grid world while inspecting utilities, greedy actions, and transition outcomes. Built around <code>Italbytz.AI.Probability.MDP</code>.</p>
		<a class="primary-link" href="gridworld-mdp">Launch demo</a>
	</article>

	<article class="demo-card accent-card">
		<p class="eyebrow">CSP</p>
		<h2>Map Coloring</h2>
		<p>Compare classic backtracking, heuristic backtracking, and min-conflicts on the Australia map while inspecting assignments, conflicts, and backtracking steps. Built around <code>Italbytz.AI.CSP</code>.</p>
		<a class="primary-link" href="map-coloring">Launch demo</a>
	</article>

	<article class="demo-card accent-card">
		<p class="eyebrow">Agents</p>
		<h2>Vacuum World</h2>
		<p>Follow the reflex and model-based reflex agents through the two-room environment and compare their action traces and performance measure. Built on <code>Italbytz.AI.Agent</code>.</p>
		<a class="primary-link" href="vacuum-world">Launch demo</a>
	</article>

	<article class="demo-card muted-card">
		<p class="eyebrow">Probability</p>
		<h2>Burglary Network</h2>
		<p>Compare exact and approximate Bayesian inference on the classic burglary-alarm network while switching evidence live. Built on <code>Italbytz.AI.Probability</code>.</p>
		<a class="primary-link" href="burglary-network">Launch demo</a>
	</article>

	<article class="demo-card featured-card">
		<p class="eyebrow">Probability</p>
		<h2>Umbrella World</h2>
		<p>Compare filtered and smoothed rain probabilities on the classic HMM umbrella sequence while revealing one day after another. Built on <code>Italbytz.AI.Probability.HMM</code>.</p>
		<a class="primary-link" href="umbrella-world">Launch demo</a>
	</article>

	<article class="demo-card accent-card">
		<p class="eyebrow">NLP</p>
		<h2>CYK Parser</h2>
		<p>Reveal the probabilistic CYK chart span by span and inspect which non-terminals survive for each substring under a toy CNF grammar. Built around <code>Italbytz.AI.NLP</code>.</p>
		<a class="primary-link" href="cyk-parser">Launch demo</a>
	</article>

	<article class="demo-card muted-card">
		<p class="eyebrow">CSP</p>
		<h2>N-Queens: CSP</h2>
		<p>Compare plain backtracking, backtracking with arc consistency, and min-conflicts repair while inspecting partial assignments, propagation, and conflict counts.</p>
		<a class="primary-link" href="n-queens-csp">Launch demo</a>
	</article>
</section>
